title: The Laura Ingraham Podcast May 3, 2016
description:
Laura Ingraham May 3, 2016 Podcast mp3

Conrad Black - National Review Contributor : "People expect the government to do a competent job and to distinguish themselves to some degree and it hasn't been happening. Donald Trump has the advantage not being complicit in any of it" Steve Hilton - CEO, Crowdpac; former senior adviser to Prime Minister David Cameron: "in this election campaign i haven't seen a clear and coherent agenda for the kind of radical conservative reform we need" Jim Bopp, Jr. - IN Delegate; President & Founder, Bopp Law Firm: "people still talk about a white knight parachuting in at the convention, i don't think our voters share that view" 


Guest Lineup
Conrad Black - National Review Contributor
Steve Hilton - CEO, Crowdpac; formerly senior adviser to Prime Minister David Cameron
Jim Bopp, Jr. - IN Delegate; President & Founder, Bopp Law Firm
Andrea Tantaros - Co-host of "Outnumbered" on Fox News (12 ET); FNC Political Analyst
